criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Aged 40-80

          2. Diagnosed with advanced PACG: meet with (1) (2) (3) or (1) (2) (4) (1) more than
             180-degree synechial closure of anterior chamber angle on gonioscopy; (2) IOP> 21mmHg
             with or without anti-glaucoma medication; (3) Significant glaucomatous optic
             neuropathy [cup-to-disc (C/D)ratio≥0.7, or C/D asymmetry > 0.2, or the rim width at
             superior and inferior temporal < 0.1 vertical diameters of optic disc); (4) With
             glaucoma visual field defects, such as nasal step, arcurat defect, and paracentral
             scotoma (on reliable Humphrey analyzer using SITA-Standard 24-2 or 30-2 algorithm);
             mead deviation ≤-12dB).

          3. Patients with clinically significant cataracts with a visual acuity of less than 0.63
             (ETDRS LogMAR), or need lens extraction assessed by an ophthalmologist;

          4. Patients voluntarily participated in the study with signed informed consent and agreed
             to follow up according to the study plan.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. History of intraocular surgery or ocular trauma (other than laser iridotomy or laser
             iriplasty);

          2. Concomitant with other types of glaucoma, including: primary open-angle glaucoma,
             various types of secondary glaucoma (secondary angle-closure glaucoma, steroidal
             glaucoma, secondary angle regression glaucoma, neovascular glaucoma, inflammatory
             secondary glaucoma, true microophthalmia, pseudoextirpation syndrome, etc.);

          3. The International Standardized Ratio (INR) > 3.0 for patients receiving warfarin or
             anticoagulant therapy before surgery;

          4. People with fundus disease that affects the collection of eye parameters or interferes
             with visual field examination;

          5. Long-term local or systemic use of glucocorticoids;

          6. Cyclops (corrected visual acuity less than 0.01 in non-study eyes);

          7. Complicated with serious systemic diseases;

          8. Pregnant or lactating women.
